From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath11k: drop data TX during firmware crash recovery

ath11k_core_reconfigure_on_crash() calls ath11k_dp_free() to release the DP
(tx_ring/idr_pool and the TCL srng) while ATH11K_FLAG_CRASH_FLUSH is set.
ieee80211_stop_queues() does not fully quiesce data TX, so a frame can still
reach ath11k_dp_tx() in that window and dereferences the freed
tx_ring->idr_pool, crashing with a NULL write:

  Unable to handle kernel write to read-only memory at virtual address 0
  pc : ath11k_dp_tx+0x1c8/0xb0c [ath11k]
   ath11k_dp_tx
   ath11k_mac_op_tx
   __sys_sendto

Guard the TX path against the crash-flush window, mirroring the guard
ath11k_ce_send() already has for the WMI path.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_tx.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/dp_tx.c
@@ -131,6 +131,16 @@ int ath11k_dp_tx(struct ath11k *ar, stru
 		     !ieee80211_is_data(hdr->frame_control)))
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
+	/* During firmware crash recovery ath11k_core_reconfigure_on_crash() calls
+	 * ath11k_dp_free(), releasing the DP tx_ring/idr_pool and the TCL srng, while
+	 * ATH11K_FLAG_CRASH_FLUSH is still set. ieee80211_stop_queues() does not fully
+	 * quiesce data TX, so a frame can still reach ath11k_dp_tx() in that window and
+	 * NULL-deref the freed tx_ring->idr_pool (and, further in, the cleared TCL srng).
+	 * Drop it, as ath11k_ce_send() already does for the WMI path.
+	 */
+	if (unlikely(test_bit(ATH11K_FLAG_CRASH_FLUSH, &ab->dev_flags)))
+		return -ESHUTDOWN;
+
 	max_tx_ring = ab->hw_params.max_tx_ring;
 
 #ifdef CPTCFG_ATH11K_MEM_PROFILE_512M
